[
    {
        "index": 1,
        "start_time": 6704,
        "end_time": 9444,
        "text": "A banker in London sends the latest stock info"
    },
    {
        "index": 2,
        "start_time": 9444,
        "end_time": 12459,
        "text": "to his colleagues in Hong Kong in less than a second."
    },
    {
        "index": 3,
        "start_time": 12459,
        "end_time": 14759,
        "text": "With a single click, a customer in New York"
    },
    {
        "index": 4,
        "start_time": 14759,
        "end_time": 16854,
        "text": "orders electronics made in Beijing,"
    },
    {
        "index": 5,
        "start_time": 16854,
        "end_time": 19082,
        "text": "transported across the ocean within days"
    },
    {
        "index": 6,
        "start_time": 19082,
        "end_time": 21603,
        "text": "by cargo plane or container ship."
    },
    {
        "index": 7,
        "start_time": 21603,
        "end_time": 23650,
        "text": "The speed and volume at which goods and information"
    },
    {
        "index": 8,
        "start_time": 23650,
        "end_time": 27486,
        "text": "move across the world today is unprecedented in history."
    },
    {
        "index": 9,
        "start_time": 27486,
        "end_time": 30581,
        "text": "But global exchange itself is older than we think,"
    },
    {
        "index": 10,
        "start_time": 30581,
        "end_time": 34170,
        "text": "reaching back over 2,000 years along a 5,000 mile stretch"
    },
    {
        "index": 11,
        "start_time": 34170,
        "end_time": 36521,
        "text": "known as the Silk Road."
    },
    {
        "index": 12,
        "start_time": 36521,
        "end_time": 39065,
        "text": "The Silk Road wasn&#39;t actually a single road,"
    },
    {
        "index": 13,
        "start_time": 39065,
        "end_time": 41134,
        "text": "but a network of multiple routes"
    },
    {
        "index": 14,
        "start_time": 41134,
        "end_time": 43494,
        "text": "that gradually emerged over centuries,"
    },
    {
        "index": 15,
        "start_time": 43494,
        "end_time": 45934,
        "text": "connecting to various settlements and to each other"
    },
    {
        "index": 16,
        "start_time": 45934,
        "end_time": 47311,
        "text": "thread by thread."
    },
    {
        "index": 17,
        "start_time": 47311,
        "end_time": 51045,
        "text": "The first agricultural civilizations were isolated places"
    },
    {
        "index": 18,
        "start_time": 51045,
        "end_time": 52615,
        "text": "in fertile river valleys,"
    },
    {
        "index": 19,
        "start_time": 52615,
        "end_time": 54905,
        "text": "their travel impeded by surrounding geography"
    },
    {
        "index": 20,
        "start_time": 54905,
        "end_time": 56521,
        "text": "and fear of the unknown."
    },
    {
        "index": 21,
        "start_time": 56521,
        "end_time": 57744,
        "text": "But as they grew,"
    },
    {
        "index": 22,
        "start_time": 57744,
        "end_time": 60541,
        "text": "they found that the arid deserts and steps on their borders"
    },
    {
        "index": 23,
        "start_time": 60541,
        "end_time": 62868,
        "text": "were inhabited, not by the demons of folklore,"
    },
    {
        "index": 24,
        "start_time": 62868,
        "end_time": 65234,
        "text": "but nomadic tribes on horseback."
    },
    {
        "index": 25,
        "start_time": 65234,
        "end_time": 68258,
        "text": "The Scythians, who ranged from Hungary to Mongolia,"
    },
    {
        "index": 26,
        "start_time": 68258,
        "end_time": 70121,
        "text": "had come in contact with the civilizations of"
    },
    {
        "index": 27,
        "start_time": 70121,
        "end_time": 73129,
        "text": "Greece, Egypt, India and China."
    },
    {
        "index": 28,
        "start_time": 73129,
        "end_time": 75517,
        "text": "These encounters were often less than peaceful."
    },
    {
        "index": 29,
        "start_time": 75517,
        "end_time": 77891,
        "text": "But even through raids and warfare,"
    },
    {
        "index": 30,
        "start_time": 77891,
        "end_time": 80719,
        "text": "as well as trade and protection of traveling merchants"
    },
    {
        "index": 31,
        "start_time": 80719,
        "end_time": 82256,
        "text": "in exchange for tariffs,"
    },
    {
        "index": 32,
        "start_time": 82256,
        "end_time": 85775,
        "text": "the nomads began to spread goods, ideas and technologies"
    },
    {
        "index": 33,
        "start_time": 85775,
        "end_time": 88576,
        "text": "between cultures with no direct contact."
    },
    {
        "index": 34,
        "start_time": 88576,
        "end_time": 91591,
        "text": "One of the most important strands of this growing web"
    },
    {
        "index": 35,
        "start_time": 91591,
        "end_time": 93160,
        "text": "was the Persian Royal Road,"
    },
    {
        "index": 36,
        "start_time": 93160,
        "end_time": 96993,
        "text": "completed by Darius the First in the 5th century BCE."
    },
    {
        "index": 37,
        "start_time": 96993,
        "end_time": 101399,
        "text": "Stretching nearly 2,000 miles from the Tigris River to the Aegean Sea,"
    },
    {
        "index": 38,
        "start_time": 101399,
        "end_time": 103937,
        "text": "its regular relay points allowed goods and messages"
    },
    {
        "index": 39,
        "start_time": 103937,
        "end_time": 108251,
        "text": "to travel at nearly 1\/10 the time it would take a single traveler."
    },
    {
        "index": 40,
        "start_time": 108251,
        "end_time": 110965,
        "text": "With Alexander the Great&#39;s conquest of Persia,"
    },
    {
        "index": 41,
        "start_time": 110965,
        "end_time": 114699,
        "text": "and expansion into Central Asia through capturing cities like Samarkand,"
    },
    {
        "index": 42,
        "start_time": 114699,
        "end_time": 117994,
        "text": "and establishing new ones like Alexandria Eschate,"
    },
    {
        "index": 43,
        "start_time": 117994,
        "end_time": 121563,
        "text": "the network of Greek, Egyptian, Persian and Indian culture and trade"
    },
    {
        "index": 44,
        "start_time": 121563,
        "end_time": 124455,
        "text": "extended farther east than ever before,"
    },
    {
        "index": 45,
        "start_time": 124455,
        "end_time": 127978,
        "text": "laying the foundations for a bridge between China and the West."
    },
    {
        "index": 46,
        "start_time": 127978,
        "end_time": 131029,
        "text": "This was realized in the 2nd century BCE,"
    },
    {
        "index": 47,
        "start_time": 131029,
        "end_time": 133306,
        "text": "when an ambassador named Zhang Qian,"
    },
    {
        "index": 48,
        "start_time": 133306,
        "end_time": 135517,
        "text": "sent to negotiate with nomads in the West,"
    },
    {
        "index": 49,
        "start_time": 135517,
        "end_time": 137605,
        "text": "returned to the Han Emperor with tales of"
    },
    {
        "index": 50,
        "start_time": 137605,
        "end_time": 140709,
        "text": "sophisticated civilizations, prosperous trade"
    },
    {
        "index": 51,
        "start_time": 140709,
        "end_time": 143909,
        "text": "and exotic goods beyond the western borders."
    },
    {
        "index": 52,
        "start_time": 143909,
        "end_time": 146313,
        "text": "Ambassadors and merchants were sent towards"
    },
    {
        "index": 53,
        "start_time": 146313,
        "end_time": 149943,
        "text": "Persia and India to trade silk and jade for horses and cotton,"
    },
    {
        "index": 54,
        "start_time": 149943,
        "end_time": 152864,
        "text": "along with armies to secure their passage."
    },
    {
        "index": 55,
        "start_time": 152864,
        "end_time": 155358,
        "text": "Eastern and western routes gradually linked together"
    },
    {
        "index": 56,
        "start_time": 155358,
        "end_time": 158323,
        "text": "into an integrated system spanning Eurasia,"
    },
    {
        "index": 57,
        "start_time": 158323,
        "end_time": 160240,
        "text": "enabling cultural and commercial exhange"
    },
    {
        "index": 58,
        "start_time": 160240,
        "end_time": 162506,
        "text": "farther than ever before."
    },
    {
        "index": 59,
        "start_time": 162506,
        "end_time": 164736,
        "text": "Chinese goods made their way to Rome,"
    },
    {
        "index": 60,
        "start_time": 164736,
        "end_time": 168281,
        "text": "causing an outflow of gold that led to a ban on silk,"
    },
    {
        "index": 61,
        "start_time": 168281,
        "end_time": 171430,
        "text": "while Roman glassware was highly prized in China."
    },
    {
        "index": 62,
        "start_time": 171430,
        "end_time": 173892,
        "text": "Military expeditions in Central Asia"
    },
    {
        "index": 63,
        "start_time": 173892,
        "end_time": 177267,
        "text": "also saw encounters between Chinese and Roman soldiers."
    },
    {
        "index": 64,
        "start_time": 177267,
        "end_time": 179547,
        "text": "Possibly even transmitting crossbow technology"
    },
    {
        "index": 65,
        "start_time": 179547,
        "end_time": 181812,
        "text": "to the Western world."
    },
    {
        "index": 66,
        "start_time": 181812,
        "end_time": 184187,
        "text": "Demand for exotic and foreign goods"
    },
    {
        "index": 67,
        "start_time": 184187,
        "end_time": 185389,
        "text": "and the profits they brought,"
    },
    {
        "index": 68,
        "start_time": 185389,
        "end_time": 187699,
        "text": "kept the strands of the Silk Road in tact,"
    },
    {
        "index": 69,
        "start_time": 187699,
        "end_time": 189989,
        "text": "even as the Roman Empire disintegrated"
    },
    {
        "index": 70,
        "start_time": 189990,
        "end_time": 193258,
        "text": "and Chinese dynasties rose and fell."
    },
    {
        "index": 71,
        "start_time": 193258,
        "end_time": 196151,
        "text": "Even Mongolian hoards, known for pillage and plunder,"
    },
    {
        "index": 72,
        "start_time": 196151,
        "end_time": 199588,
        "text": "actively protected the trade routes, rather than disrupting them."
    },
    {
        "index": 73,
        "start_time": 199588,
        "end_time": 202642,
        "text": "But along with commodities, these routes also enabled"
    },
    {
        "index": 74,
        "start_time": 202642,
        "end_time": 207087,
        "text": "the movement of traditions, innovations, ideologies and languages."
    },
    {
        "index": 75,
        "start_time": 207087,
        "end_time": 210644,
        "text": "Originating in India, Buddhism migrated to China and Japan"
    },
    {
        "index": 76,
        "start_time": 210644,
        "end_time": 212989,
        "text": "to become the dominant religion there."
    },
    {
        "index": 77,
        "start_time": 212989,
        "end_time": 216278,
        "text": "Islam spread from the Arabian Penninsula into South Asia,"
    },
    {
        "index": 78,
        "start_time": 216278,
        "end_time": 217888,
        "text": "blending with native beliefs"
    },
    {
        "index": 79,
        "start_time": 217888,
        "end_time": 220704,
        "text": "and leading to new faiths, like Sikhism."
    },
    {
        "index": 80,
        "start_time": 220704,
        "end_time": 223427,
        "text": "And gunpowder made its way from China to the Middle East"
    },
    {
        "index": 81,
        "start_time": 223427,
        "end_time": 228258,
        "text": "forging the futures of the Ottoman, Safavid and Mughul Empires."
    },
    {
        "index": 82,
        "start_time": 228258,
        "end_time": 231214,
        "text": "In a way, the Silk Road&#39;s success led to its own demise"
    },
    {
        "index": 83,
        "start_time": 231214,
        "end_time": 234272,
        "text": "as new maritime technologies, like the magnetic compass,"
    },
    {
        "index": 84,
        "start_time": 234272,
        "end_time": 237990,
        "text": "found their way to Europe, making long land routes obsolete."
    },
    {
        "index": 85,
        "start_time": 237990,
        "end_time": 240622,
        "text": "Meanwhile, the collapse of Mongol rule"
    },
    {
        "index": 86,
        "start_time": 240622,
        "end_time": 244032,
        "text": "was followed by China&#39;s withdrawal from international trade."
    },
    {
        "index": 87,
        "start_time": 244032,
        "end_time": 246851,
        "text": "But even though the old routes and networks did not last,"
    },
    {
        "index": 88,
        "start_time": 246851,
        "end_time": 248936,
        "text": "they had changed the world forever"
    },
    {
        "index": 89,
        "start_time": 248936,
        "end_time": 250848,
        "text": "and there was no going back."
    },
    {
        "index": 90,
        "start_time": 250848,
        "end_time": 253023,
        "text": "Europeans seeking new maritime routes"
    },
    {
        "index": 91,
        "start_time": 253023,
        "end_time": 255639,
        "text": "to the riches they knew awaited in East Asia"
    },
    {
        "index": 92,
        "start_time": 255639,
        "end_time": 257381,
        "text": "led to the Age of Exploration"
    },
    {
        "index": 93,
        "start_time": 257381,
        "end_time": 260488,
        "text": "and expansion into Africa and the Americas."
    },
    {
        "index": 94,
        "start_time": 260488,
        "end_time": 264286,
        "text": "Today, global interconnectedness shapes our lives like never before."
    },
    {
        "index": 95,
        "start_time": 264286,
        "end_time": 267557,
        "text": "Canadian shoppers buy t-shirts made in Bangladesh,"
    },
    {
        "index": 96,
        "start_time": 267557,
        "end_time": 270500,
        "text": "Japanese audiences watch British television shows,"
    },
    {
        "index": 97,
        "start_time": 270500,
        "end_time": 274436,
        "text": "and Tunisians use American software to launch a revolution."
    },
    {
        "index": 98,
        "start_time": 274436,
        "end_time": 278577,
        "text": "The impact of globalization on culture and economy is indisputable."
    },
    {
        "index": 99,
        "start_time": 278577,
        "end_time": 280563,
        "text": "But whatever its benefits and drawbacks,"
    },
    {
        "index": 100,
        "start_time": 280563,
        "end_time": 283246,
        "text": "it is far from a new phenomenon."
    },
    {
        "index": 101,
        "start_time": 283246,
        "end_time": 285501,
        "text": "And though the mountains, deserts and oceans"
    },
    {
        "index": 102,
        "start_time": 285501,
        "end_time": 286688,
        "text": "that once separated us"
    },
    {
        "index": 103,
        "start_time": 286688,
        "end_time": 289452,
        "text": "are now circumvented through super sonic vehicles,"
    },
    {
        "index": 104,
        "start_time": 289452,
        "end_time": 291576,
        "text": "cross-continental communication cables,"
    },
    {
        "index": 105,
        "start_time": 291576,
        "end_time": 293789,
        "text": "and signals beamed through space"
    },
    {
        "index": 106,
        "start_time": 293789,
        "end_time": 296116,
        "text": "rather than caravans traveling for months,"
    },
    {
        "index": 107,
        "start_time": 296116,
        "end_time": 297863,
        "text": "none of it would have been possible"
    },
    {
        "index": 108,
        "start_time": 297863,
        "end_time": 299385,
        "text": "without the pioneering cultures"
    },
    {
        "index": 109,
        "start_time": 299385,
        "end_time": 301842,
        "text": "whose efforts created the Silk Road:"
    },
    {
        "index": 110,
        "start_time": 301842,
        "end_time": 304115,
        "text": "history&#39;s first world wide web."
    }
]